Usage: deleteModule [-help] <hInst>+ [-cell  | -cells ]

-help     # Prints out the command usage
<hInst>+  # Name of module ((hInst)+, required)
-cell     # Deletes the module of the hierarchical instance. Error out if the
          # module is instantiated multiple times. (bool, optional)
-cells    # If the given hierarchical instance is the sole instantiation of its
          # module, then the module is deleted, along with modules whose
          # instantiations occur only inside the hierarchy with the
          # hierarchical instance as the root. (bool, optional)